{"action": "input", "code": "def draw_blue_horizontal_lines(input_grid: np.ndarray, blue_locations: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing an image and a list of tuples representing the location\n    of all blue pixels in the image. It then draws horizontal blue lines on the image at the y-coordinates of the blue pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing an image.\n    blue_locations: A list of tuples representing the location of all blue pixels in the image.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the image with horizontal blue lines drawn at the y-coordinates of the blue pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    for loc in blue_locations:\n        x, y = loc\n        input_grid[x, :] = blue\n    return input_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    red_loc = get_red_locations(input_grid)\n    green_loc = get_green_locations(input_grid)\n    blue_loc = get_blue_locations(input_grid)\n    out_grid = draw_red_vertical_lines(input_grid, red_loc)\n    out_grid = draw_green_horizontal_lines(out_grid, green_loc)\n    out_grid = draw_blue_horizontal_lines(out_grid, blue_loc)\n    return out\ndef get_red_locations(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing an image and returns a list of tuples representing the location\n    of all red pixels in the image.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing an image.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the location of all red pixels in the image.\n    \"\"\"\n    red_locations = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == red:\n                red_locations.append((i, j))\n    return red_locations\ndef get_blue_locations(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing an image and returns a list of tuples representing the location\n    of all blue pixels in the image.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing an image.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the location of all blue pixels in the image.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_locations = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == blue:\n                blue_locations.append((i, j))\n    return blue_locations\ndef draw_green_horizontal_lines(input_grid: np.ndarray, green_locations: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing an image and a list of tuples representing the location\n    of all green pixels in the image. It then draws horizontal green lines on the image at the y-coordinates of the green pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing an image.\n    green_locations: A list of tuples representing the location of all green pixels in the image.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the image with horizontal green lines drawn at the y-coordinates of the green pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    for loc in green_locations:\n        x, y = loc\n        input_grid[x, :] = green\n    return input_grid\ndef draw_red_vertical_lines(input_grid: np.ndarray, red_locations: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing an image and a list of tuples representing the location\n    of all red pixels in the image. It then draws vertical red lines on the image at the x-coordinates of the red pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing an image.\n    red_locations: A list of tuples representing the location of all red pixels in the image.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the image with vertical red lines drawn at the x-coordinates of the red pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    for loc in red_locations:\n        x, y = loc\n        input_grid[:, y] = red\n    return input_grid\ndef get_green_locations(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing an image and returns a list of tuples representing the location\n    of all green pixels in the image.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing an image.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the location of all green pixels in the image.\n    \"\"\"\n    green_locations = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == green:\n                green_locations.append((i, j))\n    return green_locations", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n  red_loc = `get location of all red pixels`(input_grid)\n  green_loc = `get location of all green pixels`(input_grid)\n  blue_loc = `get location of all blue pixels`(input_grid)\n  out_grid = `draw red vertical lines`(input_grid, red_loc)\n  out_grid = `draw green horizontal lines`(out_grid, green_loc)\n  out_grid = `draw blue horizontal lines`(out_grid, blue_loc)\n  return out\n", "gpt_code": "def draw_blue_horizontal_lines(input_grid: np.ndarray, blue_locations: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing an image and a list of tuples representing the location\n    of all blue pixels in the image. It then draws horizontal blue lines on the image at the y-coordinates of the blue pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing an image.\n    blue_locations: A list of tuples representing the location of all blue pixels in the image.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the image with horizontal blue lines drawn at the y-coordinates of the blue pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    for loc in blue_locations:\n        x, y = loc\n        input_grid[x, :] = blue\n    return input_grid\ndef get_red